1. Folder (Directory)
A folder (also called a directory) is a container used to organize multiple files and subfolders.
It helps keep files structured and manageable.
Examples:
Documents/ (contains Word files, PDFs, etc.)
Photos/ (contains images)
Projects/ (contains code files)
2. File
A file is a unit of data stored on a computer, such as text, images, videos, or code.
Each file has a name and an extension (e.g., .txt, .jpg, .pdf, .py).
Examples:
report.pdf (PDF document)
image.jpg (JPEG image)
script.py (Python script)
3. ZIP File
A ZIP file (.zip) is a compressed folder containing multiple files or folders.
It reduces file size and groups multiple files into one for easy sharing.
ZIP files need to be extracted (unzipped) before using the contained files.
Examples:
project.zip (contains multiple code files)
backup.zip (contains documents and images)
